  python -m finsmart_etl.runner full-pipeline \
    --company-guid 9489ec9a-9cea-44d6-94f3-d002b4ef341a \
    --start 2022-01-01 \
    --end 2024-12-31


----
which anomalies are missing an explanation 
!
  SELECT a.id, a.month, a.metric_name, a.severity_score
  FROM anomalies a
  LEFT JOIN anomaly_highlights ah ON ah.anomaly_id = a.id
  WHERE a.company_id = '9489ec9a-9cea-44d6-94f3-d002b4ef341a'
    AND ah.id IS NULL
  ORDER BY a.month, a.severity_score DESC
  LIMIT 50;


------
â€¢ To generate a CFO view report for a specific month, use the cfo-view command with your company GUID and the target month.

  Example for September 2023:

  cd /Users/ozgurguler/Developer/Projects/finsmart
  source .env
  mkdir -p reports

  python -m finsmart_etl.runner cfo-view \
    --company-guid 9489ec9a-9cea-44d6-94f3-d002b4ef341a \
    --month 2023-09 \
    --output-dir ./reports

  - Prints the full CFO Month View JSON to stdout.
  - Writes TR/EN Markdown reports to ./reports.

  If you want to avoid recomputing KPIs/anomalies and just use existing data, add --skip-compute:

  python -m finsmart_etl.runner cfo-view \
    --company-guid 9489ec9a-9cea-44d6-94f3-d002b4ef341a \
    --month 2023-09 \
    --skip-compute \
    --output-dir ./reports
